{
  "id": "helix-cem-mcp",
  "title": "Integrate CEM analyzer MCP server with health-scorer for component quality reporting",
  "category": "automation",
  "description": "The Helix project has custom MCP servers (cem-analyzer, health-scorer, typescript-diagnostics) in `apps/mcp-servers/`. Integrate these into the Automaker workflow so agents can query component health scores and CEM accuracy before and after changes.\n\n## What to do\n\n1. Read `apps/mcp-servers/cem-analyzer/` and `apps/mcp-servers/health-scorer/` to understand their APIs\n2. Add MCP server configuration to `.automaker/context/mcp-servers.md` documenting available tools\n3. Update `.automaker/context/CLAUDE.md` to include instructions for when/how to use the MCP health tools\n4. If the servers aren't built, add a note to run `npm run build:mcp-servers` before use\n5. Create a brief test to verify the health-scorer can analyze a sample component\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- MCP server capabilities are documented in `.automaker/context/`\n- Agents know to run health checks before and after component changes\n- `npm run mcp:health` script passes",
